		<label>Sterling L2A3</label>
		<description>Caliber: 9x19mm Parabellum. 34-round detachable mag. Select-Fire.
		
A blowback-operation 9mm submachine-gun used by the British military during the Cold War. Designed by George William Patchett during WWII, the Patchett or so-called "Sterling" SMG was meant to be a replacement for the ubiquitous Sten gun. It did not end up seeing major use during the war itself, but would be adopted in the 1950s (replacing the Sten as intended), and variations of it would continue to be used in British service well into the 1990s.\nThe L2A3 variant (called the Mk.IV at Sterling Armament Company) was adopted in 1955 only a month after the previous L2A2/Mk.III, having an improved trigger. The L2A3 would be the final major iteration on the standard Sterling designs, and saw use for almost 40 years, finally being phased out in 1994.</description>
